{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6dcf93cf-aaff-4ff9-b4c0-9cf464f63ad2","content":"The workspace is empty, so I'll give you the recommended setup based on MSTest best practices.\n\n## 1. Simplest project file with MSTest.Sdk\n\n```xml\n<!-- MyTests.csproj -->\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.7.0\">\n\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n\n</Project>\n```\n\n`MSTest.Sdk` automatically pulls in MSTest runner, assertions, and the `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` — no extra `<PackageReference>` items needed.\n\n## 2. Enable parallel execution\n\nAdd a `.runsettings` file at the project root:\n\n```xml\n<!-- .runsettings -->\n<RunSettings>\n  <MSTest>\n    <Parallelize>\n      <Enabled>true</Enabled>\n      <Scope>Class</Scope>  <!-- runs test classes in parallel -->\n    </Parallelize>\n  </MSTest>\n</RunSettings>\n```\n\nThen reference it in the project file:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n  <RunSettingsFilePath>$(MSBuildProjectDirectory)\\.runsettings</RunSettingsFilePath>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**Or**, skip the `.runsettings` entirely and use the assembly-level attribute in a file like `AssemblyInfo.cs`:\n\n```csharp\n// AssemblyInfo.cs\n[assembly: Parallelize(Scope = ExecutionScope.ClassLevel)]\n```\n\n## 3. Run database tests sequentially\n\nMark your database test class with `[DoNotParallelize]`:\n\n```csharp\nusing Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting;\n\n[TestClass]\n[DoNotParallelize]\npublic class DatabaseIntegrationTests\n{\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void Can_Insert_Record() { /* ... */ }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void Can_Query_Records() { /* ... */ }\n}\n```\n\n`[DoNotParallelize]` ensures that class runs alone — no other test classes execute concurrently with it.\n\n### Summary\n\n| Goal | Mechanism |\n|---|---|\n| Minimal project file | `MSTest.Sdk` (replaces 3 package refs) |\n| Parallel by default | `[assembly: Parallelize]` or `.runsettings` |\n| Sequential for DB tests | `[DoNotParallelize]` on the class |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7702afc5-5fcb-431a-8aaa-ae95ad5676b7","outputTokens":615,"requestId":"604C:28B932:24648D0:270B787:6A031283"},"id":"3ad370e3-7738-4f4b-8e79-11af1d417e86","timestamp":"2026-05-12T11:44:20.074Z","parentId":"81af388e-5dee-4cc2-8514-b306e1886dc8"}
